name: Reebok Ragnar So Cal
intro:
Missed the Lottery?

We have you covered!  There are still some amazing charity opportunities out there for you and your team to secure your place in history as part of one of the greatest relays to hit California!  We have partnered with local and national charities and you can learn more about them on our Extra Mile Program page HERE.  Don't miss your chance to be part of Southern California history in 2017!  Reach out to the charity that pulls on the heart strings and secure team for Reebok Ragnar So Cal 2017.  If you have any additional questions on Charitable Entries for this race please email Kyle Laudenslager at klaudenslager@ragnarrelay.com.

 

The best Southern California road trip ever, meets the ultimate running challenge. Reebok Ragnar So Cal is happening on April 7-8, 2017, and from Aug. 4th – Aug. 25th teams can enter to win a lottery spot into the race. This race is one of the most popular in the series – and for good reason!

Starting in Huntington Beach, teams of 12 (or 6) will run relay-style along bike paths, coastal trails and boardwalks with million dollar views of soaring birds and crashing waves. This 200-ish mile party doesn’t stop when the sun goes down at Dana Point. Under a bed of stars, runners continue their journey through the night. On Saturday, runners pass through famous beach towns that would make any surfer jealous; Encinitas, Cardiff-by-the-Sea, La Jolla and Mission Beach. From beach exchange to beach exchange, naturally Reebok Ragnar So Cal ends… on the beach. Teams cross under the big orange Ragnar arch together at Silver Strand State Beach in San Diego.

Bonfires, salted air, decorated vans, and a rolling carnival of happy lunatics make this race an unforgettable experience. Throw your hat in the ring, and then rub your lucky rabbit’s foot: Reebok Ragnar So Cal is the best weekend of the year, and you don’t want to miss it! Enter the lottery today!

Reebok Ragnar So Cal is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Reebok Ragnar So Cal and Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley and earn the Ragnar Republic Double Medal.

New for 2017: Reebok Ragnar So Cal will be going to a lottery!  There is a 25% team reduction and 500 spots available for the lottery. Don’t miss out on your chance to run this amazing race! Click HERE for more info!

GREAT NEWS! All 2017 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving a free pair of Reebok running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!

Any Captain who signs up for Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes is guaranteed to be selected during the 2017 Reebok Ragnar SoCal lottery. Los Coyotes Captain’s will still need to register for the SoCal lottery, but their team is guaranteed to be chosen.

Guaranteed entry to So Cal is not available for teams who transfer out of Los Coyotes.

Race Release and Waiver

As a condition of my participation in the 2015 Ragnar Relay SoCal (the “Event”) as a runner, volunteer or otherwise, I hereby covenant not to sue and agree to release from liability the Ragnar Relay Series, together with its founders, owners, officers, directors, managers, agents and employees, including but not limited to (a) Ragnar Events LLC, Ragnar Holdings LLC, Dolphin BRE LLC, Dolphin Capital Group LLC, Partnership Capital Growth Investors Direct AIV, LP Partnership Capital, Growth Investors Blocked AIV, LP, White Road Passo Stelvio Fund LLC, Clif White Road Investments, LLC and their respective officers, directors, managers, members, agents and employees;(b) Ragnar Relay race officials and volunteers; the Orange County Child Abuse Prevention Center, Monarch School, the State of California, the County of Orange, San Diego County, the City of San Diego, the City of Carlsbad, the City of Encinitas, the City of Anaheim, the City of Tustin, the City of Irvine, the City of Mission Viejo, the City of Dana Point, California State Parks, the City of San Clemente, the City of Oceanside, Oceanside Small Craft Harbor District, and (c) any and all other sponsors, suppliers, agents, independent contractors and other personnel in any way assisting or associated with this Event (collectively “Releasees”). This release is a contract with legal and binding consequences and it applies to all activities relating to the Event, whether located on the race course, exchanges or other race-related venues. I have read this document carefully before signing, and I understand what it means and what I am agreeing to by signing.

In consideration of the acceptance of my application for entry or participation as a volunteer in this Event by one or more Releasees, I hereby freely agree to and make the following contractual representations and agreements.

I know that this Event, which takes place both in daylight and at night, is held on open roads and is a potentially hazardous activity. I voluntarily assume full and complete responsibility for all risks associated with participating in the Event and for any injury or accident that may occur during my participation in this Event, including by way of example and not limitation: illness; traveling to and from the event; falls; collisions with pedestrians, vehicles, other participants, and fixed or moving objects; the effects of weather, including temperature extremes and humidity; traffic accidents; the negligence of myself and/or others, including Releasees; and road conditions, sidewalks, including darkness and surface conditions such as pot holes. I am aware of and appreciate all of these risks. I understand that both vehicle traffic and spectators will be present along the race course and that police protection will not be provided. I know that the presence of vehicle traffic during the race presents the risk of motor vehicle accidents involving participants, spectators, and/or other vehicles, and that such accidents can result in death or serious injury.

As a condition of my participation, I agree to abide by all traffic and pedestrian laws and regulations and to follow any and all of Releasees’ safety instructions, including all rules and conditions set forth in the Race Bible, which is available on the Ragnar Relay Series website, www.ragnarrelay.com. I understand that my failure to do so may result in serious injury or death and may be grounds for my disqualification from this Event.

I acknowledge that I should not enter and participate in this event unless I am medically able and properly trained. I agree to abide by any decision of a race official relative to my ability to safely complete this road race and I further agree that race officials may authorize necessary emergency treatment for me.

Having read this waiver and knowing and assuming these risks, and in consideration of the acceptance of my participation, I hereby for myself, my heirs, my executors, administrators or anyone else who might claim on my behalf (collectively “Successors”), covenant not to sue, and waive, release, and discharge Releasees from any and all claims or liability of any kind or nature whatsoever arising out of my participation in this Event, even though such liability may arise out of negligence or carelessness on the part of Releases. I hereby authorize Ragnar Events LLC, to use my image or likeness for race promotional purposes. I understand the race registration fees are nonrefundable. Teams can roll or transfer their registration to any relay (this does not include sold out or capped relays) within the next 12 months of the relay they signed up for. Using the price paid for the original team a potential charge may need to be processed based on the current registration price for the new relay. Teams that request a transfer before late registration keep the full value of their registration in transferring to a different relay. If the request is made after regular registration, $400 is reduced from their registration price ($200 for ultra) when transferring to a new relay. I have read the Race Bible and agree to abide by the rules and conditions contained therein.

I acknowledge and agree, for myself and my Successors, that the above representations are contractually binding, and are not mere recitals, and that should I or my Successors assert a claim contrary to what I have agreed to in this agreement, the claiming party shall be liable for the expenses (including legal fees) incurred by the Releasees in defending such claim. This agreement may not be modified orally, and a waiver or modification of any provision shall not be construed as a waiver or modification of any other provision herein or as consent to any subsequent waiver or modification. I consent to the release by any third party to Releasees and their insurance carriers of my name and medical information that may relate to any injury or death I may suffer arising from my participation in the Event. Every term and provision of this agreement is intended to be severable. If any one or more of them is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that shall not affect the other terms and provisions, which shall remain binding and enforceable.
charity:
2017 Reebok Ragnar So Cal Charity Team Opportunities

At Ragnar, we believe in miles. We believe the first mile, the last mile, and every mile in between teach us something about our teammates, our humanity and ourselves. Most importantly, we believe in going the extra mile. The Ragnar Extra Mile Program is inspired by generosity and compassion in an effort to help those that need it the most.

We are sorry you weren't selected for the Reebok Ragnar So Cal race, but fear not! Rest assured, there are still some alternatives for you to secure your team registration for this year.  We have partnered with several local charities in Orange and San Diego Counties, as well as a few great charities around the nation.  Through this commitment to fundraise we will extend a limited number of teams for each charity, so act fast!  We promise you, these spots won't last long so act fast and reach out to one of our amazing charities for more details.

Here's what to do!

  1. Team Captains only will reach out to their preferred charity’s contact directly (see list of charities below).  Do not reach out to Ragnar.  All initial contact requests must go through the charity.

  2. The charity contact will than respond to your inquiry with a minimum fundraising commitment and additional details of your next steps to secure your charity team.

  3. Each team will be required to create a fundraising page for the charity of their choice.  Charities will provide details of how to do this and what fundraising platforms they prefer.

  4. While teams are starting their fundraising the charities will secure a spot with us and we will then provide the captains with a Registration URL, Password and team specific Registration Code.

  5. Once the above steps are completed teams will work closely with each charity and Ragnar to help maximize their fundraising efforts.  Don't worry, you won't be on your own.  You will be part of an amazing group of runners that will help bring a charitable impact to Southern California like only Ragnarians can do!

Details vary from charity to charity so please reach out to the contact information listed in the description directly.  Through your fundraising efforts for one of the amazing charities listed below, you too can go the extra mile and be part of an amazing race this year!

 

Primary Charity for Reebok Ragnar So Cal 2017:

Orange County Child Abuse Prevention Center -

We are very excited to partner with the Orange County Child Abuse Prevention Center for the Reebok Ragnar So Cal 2017 race yet again! The Child Abuse Prevention Center is the county’s leading not-for-profit organization focused exclusively on the prevention of child abuse. The center’s early intervention programs have a well-documented record of strengthening and improving parent-child relationships, working to prevent child abuse before it occurs. Their goals are accomplished by matching families at risk of child abuse with professional caseworkers who work with them directly in their homes. The goal of intervention is to replace parenting patterns that may lead to abuse and neglect with nurturing parenting styles, as well as to empower parents to become self-sufficient. The Child Abuse Prevention Center is a 501(c)3 tax exempt entity, the fourth largest not-for-profit dedicated to the prevention of child abuse in the country and one of 100 centers nationwide sponsored in part by the National Exchange Club Foundation for the Prevention of Child Abuse. 

 

Contact Information:

OCCAPC Development Team - (714) 543-4333

Reebok Ragnar So Cal Website click HERE!

Team Faithquest - Faithquest Missions

Team FaithQuest is thrilled to be linked with Ragnar Relay for these last 9 years, directly resulting in nearly $200,000 of funds raised from thousands of small sponsorship donations of runner athletes. This fuel has been multiplied through FaithQuest’s work of engaging and mobilizing people and their churches, businesses, and schools to unite and fight together to bring tangible hope and transformation to the lost, poor, hungry, thirsty, sick, trafficked, and forgotten of the world. Our cycling and climbing events have added to this and large scale coalitions and programs in Africa, India, and now with war refugees in the middle east are championed. We’re having a blast and there is much more to do...let’s unite and do it together! 

Contact Information:

Amber Stagner

Email: amber@teamfaithquest.org

Girls on the Run - San Diego

 

We believe that every girl can embrace who she is, can define who she wants to be, can rise to any challenge, can change the world.  Can.  Our mission is to inspire girls to be joyful, healthy and confident using a fun, experience-based curriculum which creatively integrates running.  We envision a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams.

Girls on the Run honors its core values.  We strive to recognize our power and responsibility to be intentional in our decision making, embrace our differences and find strength in our connectedness.  We strive to express joy, optimism and gratitude through our words, thoughts and actions.  Nurturing our physical, emotional and spiritual health while leading with an open heart and assuming positive intent we stand up for ourselves and others.  To learn more about Girls on the Run go HERE.

Contact Information:

Karen Oliver

Email: karen@gotrsd.org

Stupid Cancer

Stupid Cancer, a 501(c)3 nonprofit organization, is the largest charity that comprehensively addresses young adult cancer through advocacy, research, support, outreach, awareness, mobile health and social media.  Our innovative, award-winning and evidence-based programs and services serve as a global bullhorn to propel the young adult cancer movement forward.

Young adult cancer (age15-39) is largely unknown in the war on cancer with 72,000 new diagnoses each year.  That’s one every eight minutes.  That is not OK!  This neglected group-now millions strong-has limited resources, inadequate support, and, more importantly, a lack of awareness and understanding from the community around them. To learn more about Stupid Cancer and how you can fight young adult cancer go HERE.

Contact Information:

Sean Shapiro

Email: sshapiro@stupidcancer.org

H.O.P.E. in California (Helping Other People Exist)

H.O.P.E. in California is a non-profit organization dedicated to providing affordable and secure housing for those in need. Our name, H.O.P.E. stands for Helping Other People Exist and that’s exactly what we do. Together, with other non-profits and government programs, we work for everyone’s right to have a safe place to call home.  To learn more about H.O.P.E. in California you can visit their webiste HERE.

 Contact Information:

Chris Whitlock

Email: cwhitlock@hopeincali.org

F.A.C.E.S.S.

FACESS (Freeing American Children from Exploitation and Sexual Slavery) is a non-profit organization that is dedicated to the care of young girls who have been rescued from sex trafficking and slavery here in the United States. It is an unfortunate misconception that this is not a problem that occurs in the U.S. But the truth is that the victims of child-sex-trafficking are from every state and every walk of life.

The fact is that over the last 25 years, this has become the third fastest growing crime in the United States. The FBI identified and recovered 850 children from sex-trafficking in 2009. There are more than 30,000 children forced into sexual slavery yet to be rescued. The average age of these children is 13 years old. Victims are recovered daily by law-enforcement, FBI, and The Department of Homeland Security.

Contact Information:

Ryan Volkommer

MDA Team Momentum

MDA Team Momentum is the Muscular Dystrophy Association’s official endurance program, created to empower individuals of all athletic abilities to train for endurance events and to dedicate their miles to help accelerate research, care, support and services for MDA families. The life-changing program provides a world-class customized training program and a committed community of MDA coaches, team members and families that inspire individuals to reach their personal goals. Every mile brings strength, independence and life to kids and adults with muscular dystrophy, ALS and related life-threatening diseases.  See more HERE.

meta_description: Reebok Ragnar Relay So Cal is one of our most popular races in the series for a big reason - the course is spectacular! Kicking things off in Huntington Beach, you'll Run, Drive, Sleep(?), Repeat under the California sunshine, beneath the stars at night, and over epic coastlines. Teams will finish and party Ragnar-style after conquering the nearly 200 mile course at our finish line party in San Diego. The ocean breeze in your hair, the sun on your shoulders, and your friends at your side at the finish line. What could be better?

exchanges.name: Exchange 12
exchanges.description:
How It Works

Van 2 will run legs 7-12, as assigned. When Van 2 arrives at Exchange 12 in Doheny State Beach, Van 1 will be waiting to begin their legs at Vista High School. Communication between Ragnar Staff, additional Race Officials, and volunteers will let Van 1 know when to begin running legs 13-18. Van 1 and Van 2 will meet again at Exchange 18. Van 1 and Van 2 should communicate as they would if they were going to meet at Exchange 12. Time adjustments will not be made if Van 1 is not prepared to begin their leg when Van 2 arrives at Doheny State Beach. Ultra Teamsand Regular teams using one vehicle will be given a time card at Doheny State Beach. The travel time between Doheny State Beach and the Vista High School will be deducted from the overall finish time.

travel.name: Special Travel Deals
travel.content:
Hotel Options

We have partnered with onPeak to provide you with hotel options for your race. Through this partnership, we are able to offer you the most competitive nightly rates at favorable hotels throughout the city and will strive to provide you with a smooth and effortless booking process when making your travel reservations. Book early with our Official Lodging Partner for the best selection!

Stay tuned for 2017's Hotel Options! 


 

Van Rental

Need to rent a van? Enterprise can hook you up!

reg_system.name: Reebok Ragnar  So Cal - VIP
reg_system.description: Reebok Ragnar Relay So Cal is one of our most popular races in the series for a big reason - the course is spectacular! Kicking things off in Huntington Beach, you'll Run, Drive, Sleep(?), Repeat under the California sunshine, beneath the stars at night, and over epic coastlines. Teams will finish and party Ragnar-style after conquering the nearly 200 mile course at our finish line party in San Diego. The ocean breeze in your hair, the sun on your shoulders, and your friends at your side at the finish line. What could be better?Reebok Ragnar So Cal is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Reebok Ragnar So Cal and Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley and earn the Ragnar Republic Double Medal.New for 2017: Reebok Ragnar So Cal will be going to a lottery!  There is a 25% team reduction and 500 spots available for the lottery. Don’t miss out on your chance to run this amazing race! Click HERE for more info!Any Captain who signs up for Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes is guaranteed to be selected during the 2017 Reebok Ragnar SoCal lottery. Los Coyotes Captain’s will still need to register for the SoCal lottery, but their team is guaranteed to be chosen.
